5. Use Container Widget with child property in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter is a versatile widget used for styling and positioning.
When using the child property, it allows you to place a single widget inside the container.

This helps in:

Wrapping UI elements
Applying styling (color, padding, etc.) to a child widget
Structuring layouts

//main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerChildExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerChildExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container with Child"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          child: Text(
            "Hello Flutter",
            style: TextStyle(fontSize: 20, color: Colors.white),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}